h3. Summary
In some instances, doing a search REST API call and ordering by entity property fails with status 500 Internal server error.

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Create an app with searchable entity properties, for example {code:json}{
  "key": "xray-issue-test-type-indexing",
  "name": {
    "value": "Test Type"
  },
  "entityType": "issue",
  "keyConfigurations": [
    {
      "propertyKey": "testType",
      "extractions": [
        {
          "objectName": "id",
          "type": "string"
        },
        {
          "objectName": "name",
          "type": "string",
          "alias": "testType"
        },
        {
          "objectName": "kind",
          "type": "string"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}{code}
# Do a search and ordering by issue.property\[testType\].*name*

h3. Expected Results
Ordered results

h3. Actual Results
{code}
{
    "errorMessages": [
        "Internal server error"
    ],
    "errors": {}
}
{code}

h3. Notes
* Doing this via UI results to a status 400 Bad Request
* Using issue.property\[testType\].*id* works while issue.property\[testType\].*name* does not, so number of issues might _not_ be the issue.

h3.Summary

When customers is using the "Get users from group" endpoint, they receive a "Internal Server Error":

{code:java}
GET /rest/api/2/group/member
{code}

h3.Investigation Done

If the URL does not use include the "startAt" and "maxResults" parameter, the REST API call will return an internal server error.

For example, calling this REST endpoint:
{code:java}
GET https://thefactore.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/group/member?groupname=jira-maconomy-sync
{code}
will return this response:
{code:java}
{"errorMessages":["Internal server error"],"errors":{}}
{code}

h3.Workaround 

Add these parameters at the end of the URL/REST end point.

{code}
&startAt=0&maxResults=500
{code}

The complete URL should look like this:
{code}
https://<atlassian-domain>.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/group/member?includeInactiveUsers=false&groupname=onduty-stronghold&startAt=0&maxResults=500
{code}

This will prevent the internal server error from being returned.
